    "\n",
    "**Motivation**: Anthropic's sycophancy paper (Perez et al. 2022, \"Discovering Language Model Behaviors with Model-Written Evaluations\") found that RLHF'd models agree with users even when the user is wrong. The question I'm poking at: *where* in the forward pass is the model \"deciding\" to be sycophantic? If it's early layers, that's different from late layers — different implications for probing, fine-tuning, and activation steering.\n",
    "\n",
